==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Westing
<hw>West"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut. & Surv.)</fld>
<def>The distance, reckoned toward the west, between the two meridians
passing through the extremities of a course, or portion of a ship's
path; the departure of a course which lies to the west of
north.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Westling</ent>⟦br⟧
